---
source: tests/cli_help.rs
expression: stdout
---
Lint term consistency in project docs

Usage: mf term lint [OPTIONS] [PATH]

Arguments:
  [PATH]  

Options:
      --article <ARTICLE>          Target a specific article by slug or title
      --root <PATH>                Mind Repo root directory
      --config <PATH>              Config file path
      --term <NAME>                Only apply/scan corrections for the named term(s) (repeatable,
                                   exact name)
      --engine <ENGINE>            ASR post-correction engine: rules (default) or lm
  -v, --verbose...                 Verbose output
      --ppl-threshold <THRESHOLD>  Minimum relative PPL improvement for LM auto-fix [0, 1) (default
                                   0.20)
  -q, --quiet                      Silence non-error output
      --fix                        Auto-fix issues that have a fixer
  -o, --output <FORMAT>            Output format [default: text] [possible values: text, json]
      --json                       Shorthand for --output json
      --rule <RULE>                Restrict to a specific lint rule kind
      --no-color                   Disable colored output
      --severity <LEVEL>           Only emit issues at or above this severity (error|warning|info)
      --max-warnings <N>           Exit 1 when warnings exceed this count
  -p, --project <NAME>             Project name for project-scoped operations
      --dry-run                    Preview fixes without writing (only with --fix)
      --include-suggested          Apply all corrections including suggested
  -y, --yes                        Skip interactive confirmation prompt
  -h, --help                       Print help
  -V, --version                    Print version
